						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into the wall of Maḷēvāḍadavara-maṭha.</p>						

						<p>Mahādēva, [1271 A.D.]</p>						

						<p>The damaged date portion of the record contains the letters <hi rend="italic">pati</hi> of the cyclic year, Śrāvaṇa śu. 6, Tuesday. This remnant may be taken to be a part of the full name Prajāpati. This cyclic year, corresponding to Śaka 1193, was the last year of Mahādēva's reign. On this assumption the date may be equated to 1271 A.D., July 14, Tuesday, f.d.t. °08.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift of land to a deity made into the hands of <hi rend="italic">Rājaguru,</hi> Chandrabhūshaṇa-yati. The deity Bhōgēsvarāditya is mentioned while defining the boundaries of the gift land. The inscription is badly damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
